.SH NAME
HTMLTextAreaElement.setRangeText \- HTMLTextAreaElement: setRangeText()
method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]setRangeText()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]HTMLTextAreaElement\f[R] interface replaces a range of text in a
\f[CR]<textarea>\f[R] element with new text passed as the argument.
.PP
Additional optional parameters include the start of the section of text
to change, the end of the section, and a keyword defining what part of
the \f[CR]<textarea>\f[R] should be selected after the text is updated.
If the \f[CR]startSelection\f[R] and \f[CR]endSelection\f[R] arguments
are not provided, the range is assumed to be the selection.
.PP
The final argument determines how the selection will be set after the
text has been replaced.
The possible values are \f[CR]\(dqselect\(dq\f[R], which selects the
newly inserted text, \f[CR]\(dqstart\(dq\f[R], which moves the selection
to just before the inserted text, \f[CR]\(dqend\(dq\f[R], which moves
the selection to just after the inserted text, or the default,
\f[CR]\(dqpreserve\(dq\f[R], which tries to preserve the selection.
.PP
In addition, the \f[CR]select\f[R] and \f[CR]selectchange\f[R] events
are fired.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
setRangeText(replacement)
setRangeText(replacement, startSelection)
setRangeText(replacement, startSelection, endSelection)
setRangeText(replacement, startSelection, endSelection, selectMode)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]replacement\f[R]
The string to insert.
.TP
\f[B]selectionStart\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The index of the first selected character.
An index greater than the length of the element\(cqs value is treated as
pointing to the end of the value.
.TP
\f[B]selectionEnd\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The index of the character \f[I]after\f[R] the last selected character.
An index greater than the length of the element\(cqs value is treated as
pointing to the end of the value.
If \f[CR]selectionEnd\f[R] is less than \f[CR]selectionStart\f[R], then
both are treated as the value of \f[CR]selectionEnd\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]selectMode\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A keyword, either \f[CR]select\f[R], \f[CR]start\f[R], \f[CR]end\f[R],
or the default \f[CR]preserve\f[R], defining how the selection should be
set after the text has been replaced.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
Click the button in this example to replace part of the text in the text
box.
The newly inserted text will be highlighted (selected) afterwards.
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]label\f[R] for=\(dqta\(dq>Example text input:</\f[B]label\f[R]>
<\f[B]textarea\f[R] id=\(dqta\(dq>
  This text has NOT been updated.
</\f[B]textarea\f[R]>
<\f[B]button\f[R] id=\(dqbtn\(dq>Update text</\f[B]button\f[R]>
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] btn = document.getElementById(\(dqbtn\(dq);

btn.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  changeText();
});

\f[B]function\f[R] changeText() {
  \f[B]const\f[R] textarea = document.getElementById(\(dqta\(dq);
  textarea.focus();
  textarea.setRangeText(\(dqALREADY\(dq, 14, 17, \(dqselect\(dq);
}
